#   2. Toggle ON the `mthamil107/memorywire` repo in Zenodo's
#      GitHub settings panel — Zenodo will then mint a concept DOI and a
#      per-release DOI every time a GitHub release is published.
#   3. Replace the placeholder below with the concept DOI Zenodo returns.
doi: 10.5281/zenodo.PLACEHOLDER
url: "https://github.com/mthamil107/memorywire"
repository-code: "https://github.com/mthamil107/memorywire"
license: Apache-2.0
keywords:
  - agent
  - memory
  - wire-format
  - vendor-neutral
  - governance
  - RAG
  - vector-store
  - MCP
abstract: >-
  memorywire is a vendor-neutral wire format and reference implementation for agent
  memory operations. It defines five operations (remember, recall, forget, merge,
  expire) over four memory types (semantic, episodic, procedural, emotional), a
  `MemoryStore` protocol that any backend can implement, and an optional
  governance channel for human-in-the-loop diff-and-approve review of writes.
  memorywire composes above existing memory frameworks (mem0, Letta, Cognee, Zep,
  sqlite-vec, pgvector) rather than replacing them, with a memory router that
  fans operations across stores and fuses recall results via Reciprocal Rank
  Fusion (k=60) with an optional one-hop graph boost.
